In this How-To, we'll cover the basics of creating a **Constraint Profile** and adding **Physics Constraints** to it.

## Steps

1. Open or [Create](Engine/Physics/PhAT/HowTo/CreatePhysicsAsset) a **Physics Asset** for your **Skeletal Mesh** using the **Content Browser**.

	![](Engine\Physics\PhAT\HowTo\CreatePhysicalAnimationProfile\openPhATAsset.png)

	[REGION:note]
	If opting to create a new **Physics Asset**, you'll need to set it up before continuing.
	[/REGION]

1. Open the Physics Asset window by using the **Window Menu** -> **Physics Asset** option.

	[REGION:raw]
	![](Engine\Physics\PhAT\HowTo\CreatePhysicalAnimationProfile\openPhATPhysicsAssetWindow.png)(convert:false)
	[/REGION]

1. Add Profile using the **+** button on the **Constraints Profile** entry, and set its name (in the image below we've named it `DocsConstraintProfile`).

	![](physConProfAddEntry.png)

1. **Close** the Physics Assset Window.

1. Using the **Profile Button**, select the desired **Constraint Profile** to edit (again, we've chosen `DocsConstraintProfile`).

	![](physConProfSelectProf.png)

1. Switch the Physics Asset Editor to **Constraints Mode** using the **Constraints** ![](physConProfConsButton.png) button.

1. Select the **Physics Constraints** you wish to include in the **Constraint Profile**.

1. Press the **Add to Current Profile** button in the **Details Panel**.

	![](physConProfAddToProf.png)

1. Adjust the settings for the selected **Physics Constraints**.

	![](physConProfAdjust.png)

1. Repeat steps 7-9 for **Physics Constraints** you desire to have in the **Physical Animation Profile**.

1. Save your **Physics Asset** using the **Save** button in the **Physics Asset Tool**.

	[REGION:raw]
	![](Engine\Physics\PhAT\HowTo\CreatePhysicalAnimationProfile\saveButton.png)(convert:false)
	[/REGION]

## Result

The **Physics Asset** will have a profile that can be called upon from Blueprint or C++ to change its **Physical Constraint** properties.



